Key Risks
Delayed Replenishments: Premium skincare stock is delayed in North and East regions, where demand is increasing rapidly, leading to only 4-5 days of cover and low fill rates. This creates high risk of stockouts and lost sales.
Demand-Supply Mismatch: Forecast accuracy of 78% coupled with rising demand trends in premium products means current supply plans may not meet actual market needs, especially in fast-growing East region.
Excess Inventory: Large excess stock ($120K) and high days cover (up to 34 days) for budget makeup and budget skincare in some regions indicate poor inventory balancing, tying up capital and increasing obsolescence risk.
Data Silos: Separate spreadsheets for sales and inventory slow decision-making, increasing risk of delayed responses to stock shortages or overstocks.
